===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Originally {{zh-l|*榦}}, a {{Han compound|倝|木|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s|t2=tree|nocap=1|nocat=1}}. The semantic {{zh-l|*木}} was replaced with a phonetic {{och-l|干}}, making both components phonetic.

===Etymology 1===
The vulgar sense entered Mandarin from {{der|cmn|nan-hbl|-}} {{zh-m|姦|kàn}}, as {{lang|zh|姦}} shares the same pronunciation with {{lang|zh|幹}} in Hokkien.

